<div class="container">

  <section class="signal-hero">
    <h1 class="signal-hero-headline">How Signal Works</h1>
    <p class="signal-hero-sub">The job search is full of silence. You apply, you wait, you guess. Signal is built to change that — starting with the work you've already done.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="signal-how">
    <div class="signal-problem-solution">

      <div class="signal-ps-item">
        <p class="signal-ps-problem">Your resume doesn't show what you've actually built.</p>
        <p class="signal-ps-solution">Resumes are summaries written under pressure, optimized for keywords. They flatten your real work into bullet points that rarely capture what you actually shipped, debugged, or figured out. Signal starts somewhere different.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="signal-ps-item">
        <p class="signal-ps-problem">Signal builds your profile from your coding sessions.</p>
        <p class="signal-ps-solution">Every time you've worked through a problem in Claude Code, Cursor, or Codex — that's real evidence. Signal processes those sessions and extracts what actually happened: the technologies you used, the problems you solved, the architectural decisions you made. No form to fill out. The work is already there.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="signal-ps-item">
        <p class="signal-ps-problem">Then it tells you honestly where you fit.</p>
        <p class="signal-ps-solution">Paste a job description. Signal scores your fit across Skills, Alignment, and Personality — grounded in your actual history, not your resume claims. An honest read in five minutes is worth more than three rounds of interviews that go nowhere.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="signal-ps-item">
        <p class="signal-ps-problem">And it works the other way too.</p>
        <p class="signal-ps-solution">Share your Signal with recruiters or engineering leads. They have a real conversation with it and walk away with a live fit score — without a resume ever changing hands.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="signal-scoring-section">

    <div>
      <h2 class="signal-how-title">The fit score</h2>
      <p class="signal-how-sub">Three dimensions, each grounded in real evidence from your coding history.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="signal-score-dim-list">
      <div class="signal-score-dim-card">
        <h3>Skills <span class="signal-score-range">0–10</span></h3>
        <p>Overlap between what the role needs and what you've actually built. Specific languages, frameworks, project types, and outcomes — not keywords on a resume.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="signal-score-dim-card">
        <h3>Alignment <span class="signal-score-range">0–10</span></h3>
        <p>Not just whether you can do the work — but whether you actually want to. Draws on what you've expressed excitement about and your stated deal-breakers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="signal-score-dim-card">
        <h3>Personality <span class="signal-score-range">0–10</span></h3>
        <p>Inferred from how you work, not a questionnaire. How you approach problems, communicate, and make decisions — matched against patterns in your actual sessions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </section>

  <div class="signal-footer-cta">
    <p class="signal-footer-cta-text">Built for developers who've been doing real work with AI tools.</p>
    <a href="/waitlist/" class="btn btn-primary">Join the waitlist</a>
  </div>

